gomodel:SYNGO_554  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Localization of Munc13 isoforms at the calyx of Held synapse.\n- Fig.1 shows localization of native protein with subtype-specific antibodies. Strong colocalization with the presynaptic marker VGlut1 together with a lack of staining of the postsynaptic MNTB cell body strongly support a presynaptic localization.\n- Fig.2/3 shows localization of genetically encoded EGFP attached to native mouse Munc13 paralogs. Strong colocalization with the presynaptic markers VGlut1 and Bassoon together with a lack of staining of the postsynaptic MNTB cell body strongly support a presynaptic localization.\n\n12/5/2017 Pim:\n- Authors state to distinguish pre- from postsynaptic localization. Literal: \"First, triple labeling was performed for GFP, the somatic protein MAP-2, and the presynaptic protein VGlut1 in auditory brainstem slices of each strain (Fig. 2). MAP-2 staining allowed one to distinguish calyceal from somatic labeling in Munc13-2-EYFP and Munc13-3-EGFP MNTB neurons (Figs. 2, 3)... Munc13-1-EYFP, Munc13-2-EYFP, and Munc13-3-EGFP signals were clearly associated with VGluT1-labeled presynaptic specializations, essentially corresponding to calyx of Held terminals (Fig. 2)....\". Experimental description: Figure 1 shows expression of Munc13-2 in mouse clay of Held synapses. As a negative control for the antibody staining calyces from Munc13-2 KO mice were used. The mice have been described previously (Augustin et al., 2001; Varoqueaux et al., 2002).\nFig.2 and Fig.3 show localization of genetically encoded EGFP attached to native mouse Munc13 paralogs. Munc13-XFP mice have been described previously (Kalla et al., 2006; Cooper et al., 2012)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_554" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

